# Commit Convention
Always start commit messages with appropriate emojis and write in English:
- ✨ feat: new features
- 🐛 fix: bug fixes
- 📚 docs: documentation updates
- 🎨 style: formatting, styling changes
- ♻️ refactor: code refactoring
- ⚡ perf: performance improvements
- ✅ test: adding or updating tests
- 🔧 chore: maintenance tasks
- 🚀 deploy: deployment related changes
- 🔥 remove: removing code/files
- 🔒 security: security fixes
- 🌐 i18n: internationalization
- 🖼️ ui: UI/UX specific improvements
- 🌟 enhance: general improvement

Format: "emoji type: description in present tense"
Example: "✨ feat: add user authentication system"

# Code Style
- Comments and documentation in Spanish
- Code, variables, and commit messages in English
- Follow ES6+ conventions